		{
			"id": 1,
			"parent": 2,
			"text": "Term translation is of great importance for statistical machine translation ( SMT ) , especially document-informed SMT . <S>",
			"relation": "bg-goal"
		},
		{
			"id": 2,
			"parent": 0,
			"text": "In this paper , we investigate three issues of term translation in the context of document-informed SMT ",
			"relation": "ROOT"
		},
		{
			"id": 3,
			"parent": 2,
			"text": "and propose three corresponding models : ",
			"relation": "progression"
		},
		{
			"id": 4,
			"parent": 3,
			"text": "( a ) a term translation disambiguation model ",
			"relation": "elab-enum_member"
		},
		{
			"id": 5,
			"parent": 4,
			"text": "which selects desirable translations for terms in the source language with domain information , ",
			"relation": "elab-addition"
		},
		{
			"id": 6,
			"parent": 3,
			"text": "( b ) a term translation consistency model ",
			"relation": "elab-enum_member"
		},
		{
			"id": 7,
			"parent": 6,
			"text": "that encourages consistent translations for terms with a high strength of translation consistency throughout a document , ",
			"relation": "elab-addition"
		},
		{
			"id": 8,
			"parent": 3,
			"text": "and ( c ) a term bracketing model ",
			"relation": "elab-enum_member"
		},
		{
			"id": 9,
			"parent": 8,
			"text": "that rewards translation hypotheses ",
			"relation": "elab-addition"
		},
		{
			"id": 10,
			"parent": 9,
			"text": "where bracketable source terms are translated as a whole unit . <S>",
			"relation": "elab-addition"
		},
		{
			"id": 11,
			"parent": 3,
			"text": "We integrate the three models into hierarchical phrase-based SMT ",
			"relation": "elab-addition"
		},
		{
			"id": 12,
			"parent": 11,
			"text": "and evaluate their effectiveness on NIST Chinese-English translation tasks with large-scale training data . <S>",
			"relation": "joint"
		},
		{
			"id": 13,
			"parent": 14,
			"text": "Experiment results show ",
			"relation": "attribution"
		},
		{
			"id": 14,
